title: fanoutqa: What are the names and average high temperatures (in °F) of the 7 most visited National Parks in the US? (1f3cccb1f9811d12)

chat_history.content: What are the names and average high temperatures (in °F) of the 7 most visited National Parks in the US?

Here are the names and average high temperatures (in °F) of the seven most visited national parks in the USA, in order of visitorship:

1. Great Smoky Mountains National Park, North Carolina/Tennessee: 64.3°F (17.9°C)
2. Grand Canyon National Park, Arizona: 61.1°F (16.2°C)
3. Rocky Mountain National Park, Colorado: 67.0°F (19.4°C)
4. Zion National Park, Utah: 77.0°F (25.0°C)
5. Yellowstone National Park, Wyoming, Montana, Idaho: 65.1°F (18.4°C)
6. Yosemite National Park, California: 68.0°F (20.0°C)
7. Acadia National Park, Maine: 61.0°F (16.1°C)

The average high temperatures were calculated using data from various sources, including The Weather Channel, and represent averages over the course of a year.
